<article id="node-4" class="node node-page odd " about="/content/privacy-policy" typeof="foaf:Document">
<div class="node-content-wrapper">
<div class="submitted"> By <span rel="sioc:has_creator"><a href="/users/armen-hareyan" title="View user profile." class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/armen-hareyan" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype=""><span>Armen Hareyan</span></a></span> Nov 11 2010 - 4:26pm</div>
<h1 class="title">Privacy Policy</h1>
<span property="dc:title" content="Privacy Policy" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
<div class="content">
<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>TorqueNews.com a Hareyan Publishing LLC company, respects your right to confidentiality and we are committed to protect your privacy.</p>
<p>Hareyan Publishing LLC EXTREMELY VALUES YOUR PRIVACY and respects your right to confidentiality.</p>
<p>Hareyan Publishing LLC gives links to third party websites for the information purpose of our visitors. TorqueNews does not control third party privacy policies and cannot be held accountable for their content.</p>
<p>TorqueNews discloses that third parties may be placing and reading cookies on our users' browser, or using web beacons to collect information, in the course of ads being served on TorqueNews.com. For this reason below we provide options to our users for cookie management.</p>
<h3>How to Customize Settings to Use Persistent Cookies</h3>
<p>1. In Internet Explorer, click Internet Options on the Tools menu, and then click the Security tab.<br/>
2. Click the Web content zone you want, and then click Custom Level.<br/>
3. Under Cookies, click the option you want to use under Allow cookies that are stored on your computer, click OK, and then click OK. </p>
<h3>How to Customize Settings to Use Session Cookies</h3>
<p>1. In Internet Explorer, click Internet Options on the Tools menu, and then click the Security tab.<br/>
2. Click the Web content zone you want, and then click Custom Level.<br/>
3. Under Cookies, click the option you want under Allow Per-session Cookies (Not Stored), click OK, and then click OK.</p>
<h3>Privacy Policy Questions</h3>
<p>Should you have any questions about the privacy policy of Hareyan Publishing LLC or with the privacy practice of TorqueNews.com please contact us by using the Contact form or write to us:</p>
<p><strong>Hareyan Publishing LLC</strong><br/>
4128 2nd St. NW<br/>
Hickory, NC 28601<br/>
Tel. 828 291-5884 or Email by using our Contact form below.</p>
</div></div></div>
